1
00:00:44,679 --> 00:00:45,640
I'm back.

2
00:00:47,039 --> 00:00:47,600
Master.

3
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,600
Look what I brought you.

4
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,479
Tianjin fried dough twists.

5
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,079
And cat's ear snacks.

6
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:54,079
So you're back.

7
00:00:55,039 --> 00:00:56,960
I'm not eating any of that.

8
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,799
That's what you say,

9
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,960
but you always end up eating a lot.

10
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:04,079
Auntie Xiaoling.

11
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:06,079
I brought this perfume for you.

12
00:01:06,959 --> 00:01:08,159
It came all the way

13
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:08,959
from England,

14
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,480
shipped over on a big steamer.

15
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:13,840
Smells nice, huh?

16
00:01:14,959 --> 00:01:16,400
It does smell like the ocean.

17
00:01:17,599 --> 00:01:18,560
Let me spray some on you too.

18
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:19,319
Go on, spray it.

19
00:01:19,319 --> 00:01:20,079
You're spraying it everywhere.

20
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:21,159
You just sprayed it into my wine!

21
00:01:21,439 --> 00:01:22,879
At least you won't smell like an old man.

22
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,959
Now you're complaining I smell like an old man?

23
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,840
Weren't you the one cuddling me to sleep last night?

24
00:01:27,079 --> 00:01:27,879
Hold on.

25
00:01:29,319 --> 00:01:30,560
Last night, cuddling...

26
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,640
to sleep?

27
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,640
What part of that

28
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:34,599
did you not understand?

29
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,439
That's great!

30
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:38,799
Auntie Xiaoling,

31
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:39,840
you know what?

32
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,359
I've waited ten years for this day.

33
00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:42,760
Come on, Master.

34
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:43,599
Let's go to a restaurant.

35
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,760
What are you so excited about?

36
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,200
It slipped out.

37
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:51,599
Just keep it to yourself.

38
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,760
Don't go telling everyone.

39
00:01:52,959 --> 00:01:53,599
You'll make it

40
00:01:54,359 --> 00:01:55,239
the talk of the town.

41
00:01:55,319 --> 00:01:56,120
I'm embarrassed.

42
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:57,640
What's there to be embarrassed about?

43
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:58,719
At your age,

44
00:01:58,719 --> 00:01:59,760
you still get embarrassed?

45
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:03,439
Does embarrassment depend on age?

46
00:02:03,519 --> 00:02:04,040
Fine.

47
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,200
I'll just

48
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,480
go fix you two a couple of dishes.

49
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,400
You two chat.

50
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,439
Master,

51
00:02:09,719 --> 00:02:10,479
tell me.

52
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,639
How did you destroy the vengeful spirit?

53
00:02:11,759 --> 00:02:12,680
As soon as I entered the town,

54
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,680
I heard people talking about it.

55
00:02:14,039 --> 00:02:14,520
Come on.

56
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,120
Pour the wine.

57
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,039
Dongsheng,

58
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:18,080
like I've always said,

59
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,080
in this world,

60
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,319
there are no ghosts.

61
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,919
That was Liu Kanshui's doing.

62
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,439
Liu Kanshui?

63
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:12,840
That's right.

64
00:03:13,439 --> 00:03:17,080
The Sorceress, your Brigade Commander's favorite.

65
00:03:17,479 --> 00:03:18,479
Back in the day,

66
00:03:18,759 --> 00:03:19,919
I killed her brother.

67
00:03:20,159 --> 00:03:23,000
She came back to get revenge on me this time.

68
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:24,719
That damn witch.

69
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,319
I'm going to shoot her right now.

70
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,360
All right, all right.

71
00:03:28,039 --> 00:03:30,080
Change that temper of yours, will you?

72
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,800
Don't jump to conclusions.

73
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:35,599
Besides, you can't shoot her now.

74
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:38,919
She's your Brigade Commander's favorite.

75
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,479
Master,

76
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,159
tell me what happened.

77
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:45,240
I have no idea how Liu Kanshui

78
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:48,000
slipped the Illusion Grass Worm to Old Zhang.

79
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,120
The Illusion Grass Worm is actually

80
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:54,199
a poisonous grass that causes hallucinations.

81
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:56,199
It looks just like a maggot.

82
00:03:56,599 --> 00:03:57,719
This poisonous grass

83
00:03:58,039 --> 00:03:59,879
has three nasty traits.

84
00:04:00,439 --> 00:04:01,280
First,

85
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,759
it sucks blood.

86
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,000
Second,

87
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:06,639
this grass is harmless during the day,

88
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:08,159
but wreaks havoc at night.

89
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,520
Third,

90
00:04:09,879 --> 00:04:11,840
it can cloud a person's mind.

91
00:04:12,159 --> 00:04:13,520
So Old Zhang

92
00:04:13,639 --> 00:04:16,240
lay here in the Bone-Keeping Temple by day,

93
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,680
and went out from here at night

94
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:18,800
to hurt people.

95
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:20,240
Then, Master,

96
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:21,839
why would this worm

97
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:24,040
be afraid of the Brigade Commander's Talisman?

98
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,920
That's all nonsense.

99
00:04:26,639 --> 00:04:28,000
It isn't afraid of his Talisman.

100
00:04:28,759 --> 00:04:29,959
That Talisman,

101
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,160
pasted on the door,

102
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,480
let Liu Kanshui know

103
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,480
who paid up and who didn't.

104
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,800
For those who hadn't paid,

105
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:37,800
Liu Kanshui

106
00:04:37,959 --> 00:04:40,399
smeared something on their doors.

107
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:43,000
What was it?

108
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,600
Shoe polish.

109
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,920
Shoe polish?

110
00:04:47,439 --> 00:04:48,360
Because Old Zhang

111
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,439
shined shoes his whole life at Yin-Yang Crossing.

112
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,240
As soon as he smelled

113
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,279
shoe polish on a door,

114
00:04:53,279 --> 00:04:54,480
he'd think he was

115
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,639
home.

116
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:57,560
Dongsheng,

117
00:04:58,399 --> 00:04:59,480
peel some garlic for me.

118
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,279
Sure thing.

119
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,399
Then what was the Talisman you gave me about?

120
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:07,120
I drew it with sulfur.

121
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:09,240
Sulfur has a strong smell.

122
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,800
It can cover the shoe polish smell.

123
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:13,480
Lao Jiugui,

124
00:05:13,639 --> 00:05:15,000
you really are a sly devil.

125
00:05:15,319 --> 00:05:16,519
I'm just a fake one.

126
00:05:18,639 --> 00:05:19,279
Master,

127
00:05:19,639 --> 00:05:20,680
I heard that night,

128
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,759
he stood when you told him to,

129
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,480
and sat when you told him to.

130
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,680
That's because

131
00:05:26,439 --> 00:05:29,000
I smeared shoe polish on the ground too.

132
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:38,800
And that...

133
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:41,000
the spell you used to set him on fire,

134
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:41,720
what kind of spell was it?

135
00:05:41,879 --> 00:05:42,680
Teach me, would you?

136
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,879
I put white phosphorus

137
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,480
inside that lantern.

138
00:05:48,319 --> 00:05:49,680
You know what white phosphorus is?

139
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,759
The moment it hits the air,

140
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,879
it bursts into flames.

141
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,959
Old Zhang

142
00:05:56,399 --> 00:05:58,000
was cursed with the worm.

143
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:59,920
Blades and bullets couldn't harm him.

144
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,839
Burning him was the only way.

145
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,279
Actually, Old Zhang

146
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,519
was also a poor soul.

147
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,240
All right.

148
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,240
Anyway,

149
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,600
that's all in the past now.

150
00:06:14,399 --> 00:06:14,959
Dongsheng,

151
00:06:15,319 --> 00:06:16,319
why did you go to Tianjin?

152
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,560
Well, our Brigade Commander

153
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,800
made a fortune,

154
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:22,399
so he took me to Tianjin

155
00:06:22,519 --> 00:06:23,720
to do a deal with the foreigners.

156
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,879
We ordered a shipment of German arms.

157
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:26,839
They said it will arrive next month.

158
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,360
Why are you acting so shocked?

159
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,480
What is it, Master?

160
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:34,319
They're buying those arms to attack Xiaolian.

161
00:06:36,439 --> 00:06:37,560
How could I have missed that?

162
00:06:38,839 --> 00:06:39,879
You have to think of something.

163
00:06:40,079 --> 00:06:41,279
Xiaolian is your sister.

164
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,120
Don't worry.

165
00:06:42,279 --> 00:06:42,959
Auntie Xiaoling,

166
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:44,480
even if it weren't for Xiaolian,

167
00:06:44,639 --> 00:06:46,519
I wouldn't let those arms harm the people.

168
00:06:46,839 --> 00:06:47,680
Good boy.

169
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,160
For saying that,

170
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,120
your Master here

171
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:51,879
will toast you.

172
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:53,279
Master,

173
00:06:54,959 --> 00:06:56,519
this is the first time you've toasted me.

174
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:58,639
What?

175
00:06:59,079 --> 00:06:59,920
You don't want to drink it?

176
00:07:00,439 --> 00:07:01,040
Bottoms up.

177
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:05,920
The Communist Party guerrillas

178
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,079
will surely set an ambush on the main road.

179
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:11,000
Load all the arms onto the wagons,

180
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:13,720
and take the back trail through Wild Fox Ridge.

181
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:18,199
This is what we call

182
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,720
a diversionary tactic.

183
00:07:31,439 --> 00:07:32,480
What are you eavesdropping on?

184
00:07:32,759 --> 00:07:33,480
Eavesdropping?

185
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,560
I'm the Brigade Commander's Senior Adjutant.

186
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,480
Do I really need to eavesdrop?

187
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,160
You really want to know?

188
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,600
I can tell you right now.

189
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,120
Those German devils' arms are really something.

190
00:07:59,399 --> 00:07:59,959
Yeah.

191
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:01,319
The ambush turned into a defensive battle.

192
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,040
It's Shuisheng!

193
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:09,959
Shuisheng!

194
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:11,279
Brothers, open fire!

195
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,399
Hurry, haul the arms over there.

196
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:36,360
Shuisheng.

197
00:08:36,759 --> 00:08:37,799
Is hugging really the only way

198
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:38,840
you know how to show affection?

199
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,360
Even if you aren't sick of it, I am.

200
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,559
I heard that under Brigade Commander Li Chuanzhong,

201
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,720
you're already a Battalion Commander.

202
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,559
Then what's

203
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:46,559
all this?

204
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,960
Even if I were the Generalissimo,

205
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,759
I'd still take my sister's side.

206
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,960
What's going on with you two?

207
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,879
We...

208
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:55,320
There's nothing to be embarrassed about.

209
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:56,639
We've become outlaws.

210
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:58,840
Clear Wind Stronghold is our home now.

211
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:01,360
We heard the Communist Party was fighting here,

212
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,519
so we came to lend a hand.

213
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,039
But I didn't expect we'd reunite so soon.

214
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:07,320
This isn't the place to talk.

215
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,559
Let's evacuate first.

216
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:09,759
Right.

217
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:10,320
Okay.

218
00:09:10,519 --> 00:09:11,120
Xiaolian's right.

219
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,320
We'll head out then.

220
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:13,120
All right, brother.

221
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:13,840
Take care.

222
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,120
If you need anything, come find us at Clear Wind Stronghold.

223
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,480
Hope you have a little chieftain soon.

224
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,639
All right, sis.

225
00:09:22,639 --> 00:09:23,399
I should get going too.

226
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:24,559
Before the Brigade Commander gets suspicious.

227
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:25,320
Okay.

228
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:25,720
Brother.

229
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,840
Send my regards to Master and Auntie Xiaoling.

230
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:29,480
Will do.

231
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,200
Maybe by the time you come back next,

232
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,600
you'll have little junior disciples.

233
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,639
What do you mean?

234
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:35,559
Nothing.

235
00:09:36,159 --> 00:09:36,559
Oh, right.

236
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:37,960
Here, take this.

237
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:40,639
For you.

238
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,399
I don't need it.

239
00:09:41,399 --> 00:09:41,879
Take it.

240
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,320
I've got it all up here anyway.

241
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,120
Thank you, Comrade Dongsheng.

242
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,240
You're welcome,

243
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:49,759
Comrade Xiaolian.

244
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:00,799
What?

245
00:10:01,279 --> 00:10:02,240
It's all gone?

246
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Who did it?

247
00:10:04,159 --> 00:10:05,080
We're investigating.

248
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:06,639
Useless fools!

249
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:07,759
Good-for-nothings!

250
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:18,320
Why so furious, Brigade Commander?

251
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,799
That shipment of German arms I ordered

252
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,440
was completely hijacked.

253
00:10:23,919 --> 00:10:25,559
Do you know who did it?

254
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:28,600
If I knew who did it,

255
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:30,120
wouldn't I have gone and taken it back already?

256
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,080
Would I need to be sitting here fuming?

257
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:34,360
I do have some leads.

258
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:37,279
What lead?

259
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,559
I suspect you have a mole by your side.

260
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,240
Who?

261
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,639
Your Guard Battalion Commander,

262
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:45,679
Dongsheng.

263
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:47,679
Impossible.

264
00:10:48,159 --> 00:10:49,279
Absolutely impossible.

265
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,559
I was afraid of leaks too,

266
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:52,519
so

267
00:10:52,759 --> 00:10:53,519
for this transport,

268
00:10:53,679 --> 00:10:55,039
I didn't use any of my own men.

269
00:10:55,799 --> 00:10:56,759
The escort team

270
00:10:56,759 --> 00:10:58,240
were all hired by the seller.

271
00:10:58,559 --> 00:11:00,320
Since you put it that way, Brigade Commander,

272
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,559
I must've overthought it.

273
00:11:06,039 --> 00:11:06,840
Sorceress,

274
00:11:08,279 --> 00:11:09,240
military matters

275
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,399
are not your concern.

276
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,039
Hurry up and think of a way

277
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,279
to make up for my loss this time.

278
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:17,519
Alright.

279
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:26,960
That made me jump!

280
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:28,440
Brother-in-law.

281
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,000
Come, hand these out to everyone.

282
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:35,000
Everyone, take a look at this flyer.

283
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,440
Let me just say a few words.

284
00:11:38,399 --> 00:11:40,799
A philanthropist from England,

285
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:41,799
an educator,

286
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,759
Ms. Maria Amari,

287
00:11:44,039 --> 00:11:45,399
is planning to open a girls' school

288
00:11:45,759 --> 00:11:47,600
in our provincial capital.

289
00:11:48,039 --> 00:11:49,320
For ages roughly

290
